Access Bank Plc, has unveiled a series of great deals and exciting offers to celebrate its customers this Valentine season. The campaign, tagged ‘It’s a Love Thing’ is the fourth edition and kicked off from February 11 to February 29, 2020. Speaking at the launch of the campaign in Lagos yesterday, executive director, Retail Banking, Access Bank, Victor Etuokwu said, “Valentine season is another opportunity to show love to our customers by rewarding their loyalty and enabling them achieve their valentine wishes. “We are using this opportunity to thank our customers for their loyalty to Access Bank. We are grateful to our customers and non-customers who depend on our banking services and products to achieve seamless banking transactions and wish everyone a happy valentine celebration.” Speaking further on the campaign, group head, Consumer Banking, Access Bank, Adaeze Umeh, said, “In the spirit of the love season, we are going to reward customers who finance the purchase of a Suzuki car through us with free vehicle registration, free servicing for a year and N100,000 fuel allowance. “We will also reward 30 lucky customers with a five-star dinner experience when they perform a minimum of five transactions on their mobile app, point of sale (POS), Web and Unstructured Supplementary Service Data (USSD) platforms.” She also said that “Customers will get 20 per cent off their initial monthly, quarterly or annual subscription when they subscribe to our XclusivePlus proposition and the first 50 customers to activate or reactivate their Diamond Business Advantage accounts will enjoy one-month free Ebony Life TV advert.” She said that instant prizes will also be given to customers who subscribe to the Bank Healthxtra plan, saying “We are offering all these and more to our customers to show how much we appreciate them for their consistent patronage.”